The paper deals with the task of frequent sequential pattern mining, which is a common problem in data mining and machine learning. The use of Answer Set Programming (ASP) is proposed as a solution to this problem. ASP is a declarative language that is often used for solving combinatorial problems, including those in the field of data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (databases), followed by cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also involves some algorithmic aspects, which could place it in the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a generic framework for sequential pattern mining with constraints, which could be relevant to the cs.SE (software engineering) sub-category.
